Why instructions improve quality

Instructions like:

think step by step

work because they cause the model to simulate intermediate reasoning tokens before answering.

That reduces errors.

This has been demonstrated in research on Chain-of-Thought prompting.

⸻

Encouragement also changes results

Phrases like:

take your time
be rigorous

shift the model toward analytical text patterns found in its training data.

So it behaves like a careful analyst rather than a casual explainer.

⸻

Context creates simulated roles

When you say:

Act as a physicist

the model pulls patterns associated with physics discourse.

So it answers differently.

